<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I hadn't noticed anyone posting on this; perhaps I missed it.  With all the chaos over dots & minstrel mezzes, I had forgotten that there was recently a blurb about "confused monsters not warping" anymore.  I logged on to Pendragon this morning & started confusing stuff.<BR>1. Confused a grey dunter & it went straight for his buddys & started munching. Repeated on a few others & the same thing...they all attacked each other & none warped north.<P>2. Confused a solo green lizard from max distance....ran staight for me & attacked.  He never flinched & ONLY attacked me...no warping.<P>3. Confused a solo green Peallaidh...same thing.  Attacked me & me only.  Didnt warp.<P>I hate to call this a nerf since I guess it is working "properly" now; however, as pathetic as we are defensively, we many of us have come to rely on this spell.  I'm so beat down from all the changes lately that I guess I don't really care anymore.  I know this is going to hurt.  At least Im 50 & don't have to PvE much any more...that's where I used it a lot.  Oh well, at least it opens up another slot on my PvE hotbar...maybe I can put amnesia in its place.  :P<P>--------------------<P>Palomides / Alat-Seldi<BR>Mezmo - Level 50 Sorcerer<BR>Siege - Level 32 Armsman<BR>Tagalong - Level 24 Full-Enhance Cleric<BR>Miracle - Level 11 Full-Rejuv Cleric<BR>Recurve - Level 10 Scout<BR>Melodious - Level 1 Camelot Vaultkeeper
