<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Tested this out today.<P> its 250-200 radius.<P> The radius is based of YOU not the Mob. For instance if you casted on a mob that was alot closer to another mob then you where the confused mob will run right for you and actually pass right through the other mob to get to you. However once you get into the 250-200 radius the confused mob will atack the other mob. This is not 100% either. Even if you confuse linked mobs all 3 linked mobs will run at you till they are in the 200-250 range at which time the confused mob will atk the other mob.<P> This is REALLY bad because if the confused mob does not do dmg you will be atkd by the other mobs because you need to be in aggro range for the confused mob to split off.<P> This combined with the "Atk you and your group only" action of confuse on guards has changed this spell to nothing more then a handy exploit tool.<P> There are alot of great exploits now for confuse however  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> <P> Imagine running around with  level 30 and a level 50 pet hehe<P> There are more but I will not mention them here  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
