<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've done some testing on this one, and I actually think it's an improvement.  Sure, it's no longer the get out of jail free card it used to be, but it's still not bad.  The big caveat is that the affected monster will only attack other monsters within a 350 radius, centered on the monster, not the player.<P>I tried it out on pygmies, pikemen, and a solo giant lizard.  The pikemen never came anywhere near me, and I was able to nuke the confused one to death with impunity.  Pygmies were a bit more difficult since they're linked, but once they were all mezzed, I could confuse a few and nuke them all to death.  Since there was nothing near the lizard, it came straight for me.  However, once I moved within 350 of another lizard, the lizard on me jumped on it, and didn't attack me again.<P>Overall, I'd tend to argue that confuse is now more useful than it was before.  It's more predictable, and involves less movement on your part.<P>Besides, this brings up opprotunities for all sorts of fun.  For example...<A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/iconduck/bonesnapper.html" TARGET=_blank>this is now possible.</A><P>--------------------<P>Sorcerer-Guinevere
</FONT>
