<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
No, the confusion factor will kick in wherever the casting sorcerer is.  My tests with the pikemen and the pygmy goblins were all from 1500 range.  The pikemen I confused all stayed where I confused them, gleefully fighting their allies.  Heck, I had to move closer to nuke on occaision.  The pygmies I fought were linked, so once I confused one, I had to deal with seven others.  Once they were all mezzed and/or confused, they acted much like the pikemen, attacking each other while I was well over 350 away.<P>This is with the level 48 confuse, however.  It is possible that you'll get different results with lower level versions.  It's also possible that I'm not understanding what you're talking about, but in all of these tests, the only time anything came anywhere near me was when there was nothing else around to attack.  I can demonstrate if you need me to, but I believe confuse is working as it should.<P>--------------------<P>Sorcerer-Guinevere
