One thing that came up while I was testing the confuse business again to make sure I was right: what are you guys testing on?  For lower level stuff, you have to be careful because of the code that was put in after that whole dragon raid fiasco that prevents confused monsters from attacking anything more than one con level higher than the monster.  I tried this out on some wood ogres and I got the same results you guys are reporting until I started confusing the beserkers first.<P>And although it sucks as proof, I submit <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/iconduck/tree.html" TARGET=_blank>this screenshot</A> as evidence that confuse does indeed work.  If you think I'm going to get within 350 of a witherwoode, you're crazy.<P>--------------------<P>Sorcerer-Guinevere
